The paper discusses a new testing paradigm for ensuring non-functional properties of compilation artifacts, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The implementation is in Haskell, which is a functional programming language, further supporting the cs.PL category. The paper also discusses the quality of libraries, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to testing, which could be relevant to computer engineering (cs.CE).
